HEADWORD: Hold up
<hw>Hold up</hw> <pr>(h⟦omac⟧ld ⟦ucr⟧p")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To rob, usually at gunpoint or knifepoint.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To delay; <as>as, bad weather <ex>held up</ex> the
satellite launch for two days</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hole</ent>⟦br⟧
